'''CareConfidential''' is a charity which provides information and counselling<ref name="grauniad">{{cite news|author=Ben Quinn |url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2011/aug/02/abortion-pregnancy-counselling-found-wanting |title=Abortion: pregnancy counselling centres found wanting &#124; Life and style |publisher=The Guardian |date=2011-08-02 |accessdate=2012-10-01 |location=London}}</ref> independent of the [[National Health Service|NHS]]<ref name="grauniad"/> on pregnancy choices,<ref name="NHS Services">{{cite web|author=NHS |url=http://www.nhs.uk/ServiceDirectories/Pages/GenericServiceDetails.aspx?id=1206198 |title=Service Directories Pregnancy Termination |publisher=NHS |date= |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref> and post-abortion support.<ref name="NHS Choices">{{cite web|author=NHS|url=http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/abortion/pages/introduction.aspx|title=Abortion |publisher=nhs.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref> They do this through their website, helpline and online chat. Information on their website and leaflets has been certified by the information Standard.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.theinformationstandard.org/ |title=Information Standard website home page |publisher=Informationstandard.org |date= |accessdate=2013-11-18}}</ref> They formerly supported a network of [[crisis pregnancy centers]], but as of 2014, no longer do so.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.careconfidential.com/Centres.aspx |title=CareConfidential Online - Pregnancy and Abortion Counselling |publisher=Careconfidential.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211194155/http://www.careconfidential.com/Centres.aspx |archivedate=2015-02-11 |df= }}</ref> CareConfidential was founded as a programme of the pro-life organisation [[Christian Action Research and Education]] (CARE), and became an independent charity in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|author=Ben Quinn |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/28/christain-activists-grab-moral-agenda |title=Christian activists poised to win concessions on abortion after 40 years &#124; World news |publisher=The Guardian |date=2011-08-28 |accessdate=2012-10-01 |location=London}}</ref><ref name="The new CareConfidential">{{cite web|author=CareConfidential |url=http://www.careconfidential.com/Newsletters/TheNewCareConfidential.aspx |title=The new CareConfidential (September 2011 Newsletter) |publisher=careconfidential.com |date= |accessdate=2013-12-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214082910/http://www.careconfidential.com/Newsletters/TheNewCareConfidential.aspx |archivedate=2013-12-14 |df= }}</ref> Since becoming independent CareConfidential do not explicitly state whether they are pro-life or pro-choice but seek to acknowledge the freedom of choice, respecting all clients' decisions.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.careconfidential.com/AboutUs.aspx |title=CareConfidential About Us page |publisher=careconfidential.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-09}}</ref>
Investigations by BBC Newsnight and by the pro-choice charity Education for Choice found that false medical information about the supposed physical and mental health risks of abortion was given during counselling at some centres affiliated with CareConfidential and that the counselling was not impartial, with counsellors pushing women to carry their pregnancies to term.<ref name="grauniad"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/newsnight/9577247.stm |title=Newsnight - Can abortion advice be independent and impartial? |publisher=BBC News |date=2011-08-31 |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=brkgRnLWbZ8 Newsnight]</ref> Other centres were impartial, offering clients the time, space and accurate information to talk though their choices.<ref name="grauniad"/><ref name="mail"/> An investigation by the Daily Mail noted that although some counsellors might have received training and accreditation, there is no legal requirement for counsellors to have any credentials at all.<ref name="mail">{{cite news|author=Jenny Stocks |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2031572/Abortion-Mail-writers-investigation-counselling-services-poses-disturbing-questions.html |title=Abortion: Mail writer's investigation into counselling services poses disturbing questions &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date= 2011-08-30|accessdate=2012-10-01 |location=London}}</ref>
