'''Ease of Access Center''', formerly '''Utility Manager''', is a component of [[Windows NT]] family of operating systems that enables use of [[Assistive technology|assistive technologies]]. Utility Manager is included with [[Windows 2000]] and [[Windows XP]]. In [[Windows Vista]], Utility Manager was replaced with the Ease of Access Center [[Control panel (software)|control panel applet]], which is still included in [[Windows 10]], [[Microsoft]]'s latest [[operating system]]. The keyboard shortcut for invoking Utility Manager or the Ease of Access Center is {{keypress|Windows|U}}. The [[command-line interface|command-line]] shortcut (used in [[Windows Command Prompt]] or [[Run command]]) is <code>utilman</code>.

Some features include [[Microsoft Narrator|Narrator]], [[Magnifier (Windows)|Magnifier]], [[High Contrast (accessibility feature)|High Contrast]], [[On-screen keyboard|On Screen Keyboard]], [[Sticky keys|Sticky Keys]], [[ToggleKeys|Toggle Keys]], [[FilterKeys|Filter Keys]], and [[Mouse keys|Mouse Keys]].

