{{Infobox lake | name = Lac de Chambon | image = Barrage d'Éguzon (36) - Crête - rive droite - 2.jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Indre]] ([[Centre-Val de Loire]]) | coords = {{coord|46|26|12|N|1|36|50|E|region:FR_type:waterbody}} | lake_type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = [[Creuse River]] | outflow = [[Creuse River]] | catchment = | basin_countries = France | length = {{convert|16|km|abbr=on}} | width = | area = {{convert|312|ha|abbr=on}} | depth = {{convert|18.6|m|ft|abbr=on}} | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|58|e6m3|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | sections = | cities = | frozen = }} The '''Lac de Chambon''' (''Chambon Lake'') is an artificial [[lake]] on the [[Creuse River]], [[France]], created by the [[Eguzon dam]], a [[hydroelectric dam]]. Beaches have been created around the lake, the largest in the Centre Region. There is a sailing school on the lake near [[Eguzon]]. [[Canoe]]s, [[kayak]]s and [[pedalo]]s can be hired in season. The lake is also very popular with [[waterski]]ers and anglers.
It is not to be confused with [[Lac Chambon]] in the [[Puy-de-Dôme]] department or [[Lac du Chambon]] in the [[Isère]] department.
